Is it a noisy fan? Everyone's sensitivity to sound is different. The noise level of our fan is 45 dB. A suitable living environment should not exceed 55 dB and not fall below 15 dB. Is the portable fan rechargeable? Yes, the small fan has built-in rechargeable 4000mAh batteries and a USB Type-C input for charging. Great for outdoor use. Would this stroller fan clip on for baby stroller? Yes, The tripod are super flexible and strong. You can easily attach it to the stroller. Does this clip on stroller fan have an oscillation function? Yes, It can oscillate 45° and covers a range of 135°. I need a clip fan for my baby. Does this fan have chemicals? No, our fan contains no harmful chemicals. It is safe for babies and pets.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best fan for baby
reviews.reviewText: This is the best fan for babies or even older children and adults who might want a fan for outdoors.. love that it’s rechargeable and has multiple speeds. Especially that you can actually feel the fan blowing unlike other portable fans out there. Also, this fan oscillates! And has a light that’s pretty bright. 10/10 recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best bang for your buck.
reviews.reviewText: So happy I bought this product. I used this fan as a stroller fan for my baby in the Texas heat. She loves this fan and it really helped keep her cool in 90+ degree weather.It has multiple speed settings and can run for hours on one charge (Yes! It’s rechargeable!) I love not having to buy batteries. This fan has some serious grip to it! Used it on walks, attached it to the stroller, lawn chairs, you name it! I had people asking me where I got it. It’s durable made with hard plastic that I would not expect to break when dropped. It’s heavy for a portable fan but the grips hold it up very well and is super easy to adjust.Stop looking, you’ve found what you need!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I <3 this fan!!
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a fan to use in a classroom. I needed a portable fan with rechargeable battery as I am not always subbing in the same room. I've wasted too many AA batteries with other handheld fans and the kind worn around the neck. (Fans are classroom must have when it's not A/C season.)So, I bought this fan after I bought a similar one that was not oscillating. For a few dollars more, I now have an oscillating fan with a natural wind function in addition to low, medium, and high speed. I've used this as a tripod (hat tip: use the rear leg to steady the front by bending it like a fish hook facing outward). Also, I've used this with its legs wrapped securely around a wooden TV tray leg.PROS:• All the fan speeds serve a purpose and function very well!• Oscillating on a handheld fan! Are you kidding me?!• Long battery life (be prepared to charge more often if using highest speed)• Can operate while charging! Seriously!• Very bendy, strong legs!• Can twist off faceplate to cleanCONS:• Does not have a separate on/off switch (so be careful how it's packed to avoid accidentally running the fan)• No battery percentage indicated (this would be a major bonus)• No advanced notice the fan will stop (when battery is on empty, it stops... This is why a battery meter would be handy)Otherwise this fan is perfect! Get it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I use this as a carseat fan. Pretty easy to use and portable. The legs can be wrapped around the bar of the carseat and stays in position well. The light is good, use it to see my child in a seat mirror when it is dark outside and driving. Can be charged via USBC, which is great. The durability could be worked on, seems like it wouldn't hold up to a high or multiple drops. But at the price point, can't complain.
